      "title": "Form IX Verbs (اِفْعَلَّ)",
      "titleArabic": "باب اِفْعَلَّ",
      "content": [
        "Form IX verbs are formed by prefixing اِ and doubling the third radical. This pattern is exclusively used for colors and physical defects."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: اِفْعَلَّ (if'alla) - with doubled third radical",
        "Maṣdar pattern: اِفْعِلَال (if'ilāl)",
        "Used only for colors and physical defects",
        "All Form IX verbs are intransitive"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِحْمَرَّ", "english": "to become red" },
